description:
I make videos to entertain—and sometimes to give people a quick break from everyday stress.
This is primarily a gaming channel, with a focus on scary and suspenseful content.
You’ll find gameplay, horror shorts, Backrooms-inspired scenes, occasional AI and animation work—and sometimes, just animals or quiet moments of calm.
Some videos are intense, others more relaxed. I try to keep things interesting.
Thanks for watching—and for being part of what I’m building here.

description:
Herzlich Willkommen auf meinem Kanal !
ich lebe in Deutschland ( Bayern ) und beschäftige mich mit dem Thema Video/Foto schon seit einiger Zeit. Meine aktuellen Kameras sind die Panasonic Lumix GX 80, Lumix G70, Lumix G5, die neue DJI OSMO Pocket 3, Yi 4K Plus (Actioncam) die GOPRO HERO 8 BLACK (Actioncam) und die neue Insta360 X4 (360 Grad Kamera). Für Luftaufnahmen kommt seit Anfang April 2023 die DJI Air 2s und die dafür passende fliegende 360 Grad Kamera Insta360 Sphere zum Einsatz. Ich filme heute fast nur noch in 4K. Die Filmthemen die mich interessieren sind sehr breitgefächert, dass sind sowohl Reisefilme ( weltweit ), Filme von Motorsportveranstaltungen aber auch alles andere Interessante. Für Verbesserungsvorschläge und Anregungen bin ich immer offen und nehme Kritik auch gerne an.

description:
Slow Motion videos of nature, explosions, and more can be found on the first slow motion channel on YouTube! .

From silly to science, Emmy Award winner Alan Teitel and his UltraSlo Studio create compelling slow motion video images for online entertainment and education. Slow motion videos from the Ultraslo stock video library are used in documentaries commercials and scientific research world wide. Slow motion videos from UltraSlo have been viewed oner a quarter of a billion times on all the sites that love to stream  slow motion videos around the world

Alan has a unique outlook and viewing perspective based on his twenty-five years of slow motion and 3d work which allow him to see the world at a much different speed. Alan is a director, cinematographer and producer of national commercials, documentaries, and dramatic scenes. 

Alan won two Emmy's for Cinematography and Technical Achievement. Alan has been nominated six times for his outstanding work on broadcast television

description:
Playing with RC helicopters as I am not young enough nor wealthy enough to try real ones, and a good thing this may be as I seem to crash a lot, and certainly crashing an RC helicopter is way better than crashing a real one ;) I also have a few small and larget quadcopters now, and a light RC airplane.
If you snoop through all my movies (yes, it's a lot of almost the same) you'll see how (if) I progressed. Was and stil is an interesting journey.
I got few videos of my kids, but majority of them are on my wife's channel: http://www.youtube.com/aniatokarski
Yes, we got 2 parakeets - that roam free in our house - you will see some videos of these...; and, this will be a shocker! We got a kitten not long ago.. wise? NOT! Fun? Heck yes! Worried about birds... well, yes.. ;)
So the focus of this channel is heavily moving from aviation into.. Kittation maybe?  I am becoming a CatCrazyLady.. I fear.... ;)

description:
mGSM.pl jest serwisem zajmującym się szeroko pojętą tematyką GSM, ale skupiającym się przede wszystkim na najbardziej namacalnych i powszechnie dostępnych tej technologii przejawach - na telefonach komórkowych.

Byliśmy przy narodzinach technologii mobilnych w Polsce, współtworzyliśmy rynek, a jako serwis internetowy poświęcony telefonom istniejemy od 2005 roku - i od tej pory staramy się dostarczyć użytkownikom Internetu jak najbardziej rzetelną informację o specyfikacji technicznej dostępnych na rynku urządzeń. Nasze dane są oparte na dokumentacji producentów i ilustrowane, jeśli to tylko możliwe, dużymi oficjalnymi zdjęciami prasowymi poszczególnych modeli.

Na mGSM.pl można nie tylko porównać poszczególne modele, czy odnaleźć testy telefonów i aktualności ze światka GSM, ale również wypowiedzieć się o posiadanym telefonie i znaleźć pomocną dłoń dzięki systemowi moderowanych komentarzy.

description:
Welkom op mijn kanaal!

Op mijn kanaal zul je voornamelijk natuurvideo's vinden, gefilmd in binnen en buitenland. Dit kan zowel in natuurparken als diertuinen zijn, maar voornamelijk in niet omheinde gebieden waar iedereen in kan. Ook heb ik verschillende slow motion filmpjes op mijn kanaal staan gefilmd met 200fps in VGA kwaliteit. Geen hoge kwaliteit, maar toch mooi om naar te kijken en de meeste met 100fps in HD kwaliteit. In principe staat in elke omschrijving waar iets precies gefilmd is, wil je toch ergens wat meer over weten, laat dan even een berichtje achter in het commentaar gedeelte.

Veel plezier!


Welcome on my channel!

On my channel you will see that most of my video's are about nature/animals that are filmed in and outside the Netherlands. You can also find some slow motion videos filmed at 200fps VGA (640x480) and 100fps HD (720p). If you want to know something about my vids that's not in the description, please leave a comment.

Have fun!

description:
To provide quality slow motion videos of baseball pitchers, hitters mechanics and use them as teaching tools when working with students!
Our eyes only see 30 frames per second so when you look at something at full speed, we can only guess what is really going on. When we look at it in slow motion, you are able to see exactly what is going on. Thus, improving teaching quality. I teach hitting and pitching mechanics and use my video library to inspire my students. Please use this library for the same purpose and spread the word!

I’m taking over this channel from my dad, Jerry Miculek – one of the greatest shooters of all time – and bringing you into the next chapter of our story. This is where pro-level shooting meets everyday joy, ridiculous challenges, inspiring stories, and a whole lot of fun. It’s all about community and building our Trigger Tribe – where everyone is welcome, encouraged, and inspired to grow, play, and laugh with us. 

You’ll find: 
🎯 My life as a pro shooter (and proud goofball) 
🔥 Behind-the-scenes training & world-level competitions 
❤️ Inspiring stories & wild challenges 
💡 Firearms education with heart 
🎥 Vlogs with family, friends & Trigger Tribe guests. 

The range can be more than targets — it can be a place of confidence, connection, and belonging. That’s the world I want to build. Welcome to the Trigger Tribe. Let’s do this together!

description:
Videomaker novellino. Cultore dell' edonismo automobilistico, pur essendo un gran pezzente.

Troverete principalmente video degli eventi motoristici che mi capitano tra Varese, Como e Milano.. e altre cose molto cazzare!


I miei video hanno l'intento, invece, di celebrare ogni attimo di quello che può essere portare una motocicletta, traversare una curva, saltare una duna, vedere l'escursione di una sospensione, lo slittamento degli pneumatici su sterrato.

Il tutto al rallentatore con sottofondo musicale.

description:
When I was a young boy (1950's), I learned to play golf by closely watching the best players at the course I grew up on. I would then stand in front of a window and copy their swings... then I would go to the practice area to ingrain that look and new feeling to muscle memory. That WAS and STILL IS a great way to learn! It's called SELF-DISCOVERY! 

When you discover a helpful motion or thought ALL BY YOURSELF, YOU WILL NEVER FORGET IT! - I never have!  

At the age of 78, I'm still a mid single-digit player. My goal with this YouTube channel is to provide a platform for TEACHING and LEARNING! I will provide videos and detailed descriptions of the finest golfers in the world, their swings and some of their finest shots so YOU can learn and improve as I have. 

The focus here is geared toward TEACHING and LEARNING the short game (putting, chipping, pitching and wedge play from 120-yards in), but you will also see some of the finest, Tour-Proven full swings and descriptions as well.⛳️

description:
Sharing things we learn while wrenching on Corvettes, other cars and whatever needs building or fixing! 

My dad loved cars and was an exceptional mechanic. He used to say that we could fix just about anything if we took the time to read, learn and then proceeded with patience and care. Now we can learn even faster with videos! My dad helped me immensely, I learned so so much from him, and the hours spent leaning over hoods or building or fixing things around the house are some of my fondest memories with him. Now my oldest son has become a great mechanic too - and I probably learn more from him than he does from me! So this channel is us trying to pay it forward and help others. We hope it’s helpful to you!

Note: We're always learning and welcome feedback, guidance and advice!

I'm Rob (the dad). Ray is my late father. My middle name is Raymond and my funny southern name is "Bobby Ray”.

My sons are Andrew, Mark and Ryder and currently (Nov 2022) they're ages 23, 18 and almost 10.

Regards

Billy the Artist.

description: He worked with Chris Hopewell and Ben Foley at Collision films (the animation specialists) for 8 years and was involved with shooting various music promos for bands such as Radiohead, Run The Jewels, Scissor Sisters, Kula Shaker, McFly, The Bees and The Offspring. With Chris he then went onto shooting a stop motion sequence for A Fantastic Fear of Everything which stars Simon Pegg. Another local company (Bolex Brothers) invited Jon to help shoot a Pilot for The Freak Brothers movie. Recently Jon has been filming on varied projects for companies such as Samsung, Powerade, Wonga, Orange, Glaxo and Waitrose as well as working on his own projects for many of Bristol's graffiti artists. He now offers full video production for any projects! Just to mix things up he has been working for the past 18 years in over 50 episodes of Doctor Who, where he performs as many of the infamous monsters. These include Daleks, Cybermen, Judoon, Ood, Whispermen, Hath, Heavenly Host and Mire.

description:
Hope you enjoy my channel; among my many hobbies, I'm an amateur photographer (Nikon D7000, DSLR), videographer (GoPro Hero 3 x 2), and group / event organizer of 100+ member motorcycle ride group!  Primarily lead rider every Sunday in the beautiful Southern California mountains / environs (typically 200 - 300 miles per ride).  Formerly, I put 54,000 miles on my Harley VROD, Night Rod Special, and in January I upgraded to a 2013 Yamaha FJR 1300!  

My channel focuses on scenic motorcycle rides / byways such that the viewer will have an excellent perspective of the route and roadside National and State Parks, attractions, and points of interest.  As well, on occasion, we take 1,000 to 3,000 mi overnight rides featuring mountain and canyon rides to AZ, NV, CO, UT, and OR.

An "East Coaster" originally, I have resided in several locations in the US, as well as 8 years in Europe, and lucky to currently live in Dana Point ..... with some of the best weather in the country!

Trust what you FEEL!

One of the biggest privately owned Studios in India – Yash Raj Films (YRF).
In the last four decades, YRF has grown from strength to strength and is the country’s premier independent Studio conglomerate. The company's core lies in the production and distribution of some of the industry's top grossing films and today has India's most enviable film catalogue. With offices in New York, London, and Dubai, YRF handles its own global distribution of films. YRF has its own state-of-the-art fully integrated Studio. It has recently forayed into the International space with YRF Entertainment. The company has its own music and home entertainment labels, design cell and post-production facilities, marketing, digital, licensing, merchandising and talent management divisions, as well as in-house units focused on the creation of television software, ad films and music videos. YRF is an integral part of the entertainment business in India.

description:
A bath of silicon oil is vibrated and oil droplets are deposited on the surface. Thanks to the vibrations, the droplets do not coalesce, but bounce on the surface.

For specific values of amplitude and frequencies, the droplet start to move forward by itself : while bouncing, it create waves with which it interacts.

This object has been called a walker, and exhibits properties reminiscent of an elementary particle, because it is at the same time a particle (the droplet) and a wave (The local standing wave pattern created by the droplet)

description:
Pocket-lint is a digital publication that launched in 2003. We are proud to have become a trusted global authority on consumer tech. Our work has been quoted in marketing materials for the likes of Samsung, Apple, Sky, and LG.

We are focused on consumer tech and gadgets, offering news, in-depth analysis, and buyer's guides for smartphones, smart homes, cameras, and the latest advances in similar technologies.

We have been at the forefront of significant technology shifts, from the rollout of 3G to the first iPhone to the product reveals for all the latest game consoles.

At the heart of Pocket-lint is our editorial team, a group of seasoned consumer tech experts who have dedicated years to the consumer tech space. Their expertise ensures that every article we publish is a reliable source of information, delivering exactly what consumers need to know.

Pocket-lint is owned and operated by Valnet Inc.

Join me — let’s make every moment an adventure.

description:
My YouTube Philosophy- 

I love making YouTube videos because I love creating content. Making videos is a form of art to me, and putting them out in the world for anyone to see is a passion/hobby of mine. 

​I have been making videos for 8 years since January 9, 2011 and love every bit of creating them.
I love that you can upload anything to YouTube, and get noticed in some way. YouTube is amazing! 

Over the years, I have mastered multiple video editing programs to create my videos. First program being 'Splice Video Editor'. I then moved on to a very similar editor called 'Perfect Video Editor' which let me do a tiny bit more with my video projects. I then moved onto iMovie back in October 2015 which let me make cuts and do various other details to my videos.

​I plan to start using a much bigger program such as Final Cut Pro X or Adobe Premier in the future! 

Enjoy my channel!

description:
The popular YouTube channel Quint BUILDs originally made in-depth engineering videos on something called GD&T.  It's a standard published by ASME (American Society of Mechanical Engineers) used to define fits of manufactured parts.  Quint has a senior level certification in GD&T and originally made videos to help others understand it.  They're all here FREE for anyone looking for help on that topic.  You may still see new content here but most of Quint's effort is currently directed to Quint BUILDs.  That content is more appealing to a general audience which is why it gets MILLIONS of views rather than thousands.  
 
If you gained something from these videos and want to give back, you can make a one time contribution on PayPal:  qcrispin@gmail.com  or consider becoming a patron of Quint BUILDs.  

There's also one piece of pay-only content, a study guide Quint created based on the free videos.
Find more on that here:  https://youtu.be/WLQJ8q_zpA0

Thanks and good luck learning GD&T!
